{"TopicId":155916,"ForumId":69,"TopicTitle":"Problem with the IVA Camera","CreatedByName":"Vesaugh","CreatedById":161683,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-03T00:31:01Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Vesaugh","CreatedById":161683,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-03T00:31:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EI have a Problem with my IVA Camera, as you can see the normal camera in IVA must look like this:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022QRYAfEl.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022562\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/QRYAfEl.png\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EBut mine camera is looking like this :\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u00223mItmX3.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022562\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/3mItmX3.png\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EI Already tried everything, adjust the FOG, reistall\u00A0the game, in the screen shots i used mods but this bug still occur in KSP Stock, my current version is 1.2.2 and this bug appeared only after 1.1\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EHelp-me guys it may seem not a big problem but i play\u00A0a lot in IVA and this occur in every cockpit, the camera looks like is stupid high in some and this is freaking me out i can\u0027t even see the flight instruments in some.\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003ESorry for my poor English :v\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sal_vager","CreatedById":16426,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-03T10:22:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/161683-vesaugh/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022161683\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/161683-vesaugh/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Vesaugh\u003C/a\u003E, please try a stock game with a new save, and with the settings reset to their defaults, you can find a reset button in the settings screen.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you still have this issue after that let me know.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHope this helps \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vesaugh","CreatedById":161683,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-03T12:08:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EHi \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/16426-sal_vager/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002216426\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/16426-sal_vager/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@sal_vager\u003C/a\u003E, I took all the mods, reset all settings and the bug still persist as you can see.\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Arpv41v.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022560\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/Arpv41v.png\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E(I use the mk1 cockpit because the camera is the worst in him)\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EI was kind of expecting this\u00A0cause i already re-installed the game and the bug hasn\u0027t go away\u003C/strong\u003E ;-;\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sal_vager","CreatedById":16426,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-03T12:25:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222943231\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022155916\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221486123691\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022161683\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Vesaugh\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n15 minutes ago, Vesaugh said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents ipsClearfix\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EHi \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/16426-sal_vager/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002216426\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/16426-sal_vager/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@sal_vager\u003C/a\u003E, I took all the mods, reset all settings and the bug still persist as you can see.\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E(I use the mk1 cockpit because the camera is the worst in him)\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EI was kind of expecting this\u00A0cause i already re-installed the game and the bug hasn\u0027t go away\u003C/strong\u003E ;-;\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOkay Vesaugh, please see this thread we\u0027ll need your game logs to know more.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/83213-stock-support-bug-reporting-guide/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vesaugh","CreatedById":161683,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-03T12:35:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nx64\u00A0log\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.dropbox.com/s/lmwjwf5xakvu7e3/output_log.txt?dl=0\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.dropbox.com/s/lmwjwf5xakvu7e3/output_log.txt?dl=0\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sal_vager","CreatedById":16426,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-03T12:47:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222943257\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022155916\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221486125306\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022161683\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Vesaugh\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 minutes ago, Vesaugh said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents ipsClearfix\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nx64\u00A0log\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.dropbox.com/s/lmwjwf5xakvu7e3/output_log.txt?dl=0\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 target=\u0022_blank\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.dropbox.com/s/lmwjwf5xakvu7e3/output_log.txt?dl=0\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNevermind, I remember, it\u0027s the difference in eye offset between male and female Kerbals, if you want the lower view you need to use a female.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vesaugh","CreatedById":161683,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-03T12:54:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/16426-sal_vager/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002216426\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/16426-sal_vager/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@sal_vager\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0Thx for the help XD\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sal_vager","CreatedById":16426,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-03T13:02:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGlad I could be of assistance \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Overland","CreatedById":119812,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-08T11:57:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNoticed this bug myself on a stock install - I drive IVA primarily . can confirm a bit disappointingly it is the eye level of female/male kerbal differences\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nkind of rules out female kerbals driving my trains.. confuses me a bit why this was done? unless their planning first person kerbal in next update?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMark 1 inline hasn\u0027t got any difference between the 2 genders - mark 2 inline has - the male looks as though their eyeballs are glued to the cealing where the female gives a more traditional IVA view\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://imgur.com/a/soKyl\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://imgur.com/a/soKyl\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-02-08T11:58:37Z\u0022 title=\u002202/08/2017 11:58  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 8, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Overland\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"paulprogart","CreatedById":174587,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-08T20:46:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI was just in settings.cfg for something else and happened to see these settings and they reminded me of this thread.\u00A0 I don\u0027t see this mention of this above so I thought I\u0027d pass it on it in case those affected want to try adjusting them.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Courier New\u0027, Courier, monospace;\u0022\u003EFEMALE_EYE_OFFSET_X = 0\u003Cbr\u003E\nFEMALE_EYE_OFFSET_Y = 0.009083331\u003Cbr\u003E\nFEMALE_EYE_OFFSET_Z = 0.03378779\u003Cbr\u003E\nFEMALE_EYE_OFFSET_SCALE = 2.03\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere are no settings for male offsets, so presumably to match the male eyes you would make them all 0s?\u00A0 \u0026lt;shrug\u0026gt;\u00A0 That\u0027s a guess.\u00A0 Anyhow the values above are the defaults from my config.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"luizopiloto","CreatedById":97503,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-08T21:46:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthe internal cfgs have a camera offset parameter that was added recently... \u0022kerbalEyeOffset = 0, 0.02, 0\u0022\u003Cbr\u003E\nit moves up the original POV camera.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you have \u003Cu\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/50533-121-module-manager-275-november-29th-2016-better-late-than-never/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EModule Manager\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/u\u003E installed, you can create a .cfg file and place it inside GameData folder with the following code:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode\u0022\u003E\n@INTERNAL[mk1CockpitInternal]\n{\n\t%MODULE[InternalSeat]\n\t{\n\t\t%kerbalEyeOffset = 0, -0.015, 0\n\t}\n}\n@INTERNAL[mk1InlineInternal]\n{\n\t%MODULE[InternalSeat]\n\t{\n\t\t%kerbalEyeOffset = 0, 0.01, 0\n\t}\n}\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}